{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b6e1d2a0-7c44-4f2e-9d11-luke-auth-gw-0001",
    "name": "Luke — Engine via Auth Gateway",
    "description": "Access luke-core-engine resources through luke-auth-engine (the consumer auth gateway).\n\n## Two ways in\n1. **Via Gateway** (`{{authBaseUrl}}`) — send a **Clerk session JWT** as a Bearer token. The gateway verifies it, resolves the user, mints a signed act-as-user token, and proxies to the engine. This is how the consumer app talks to the engine. Collection-level auth = `Bearer {{clerkJwt}}`.\n2. **Direct to Engine** (`{{engineBaseUrl}}`) — operator/admin endpoints (onboarding, tenant/group admin) use **HTTP Basic** and CANNOT go through the gateway (it only accepts Clerk Bearer). The `Engine Admin (DIRECT)` folder overrides auth to Basic and targets the engine directly.\n\n## Getting a Clerk JWT for `{{clerkJwt}}`\nThe gateway expects a real Clerk session token. Easiest ways:\n- Open the consumer UI in a browser, sign in, open DevTools console and run `await window.Clerk.session.getToken()`, copy the value.\n- Or copy the `Authorization: Bearer …` value from any network request the signed-in app makes.\nClerk session tokens are short-lived (~1 min) — re-fetch when you get 401s.\n\n## First-run gotcha: onboarding\nA Clerk user who has authenticated but was never onboarded gets **403 \"not provisioned\"** from the engine. Run `Engine Admin (DIRECT) → Onboard Clerk User` (operator Basic auth) once per user first. `clerkSub` there must equal the Clerk token's `sub` — the gateway maps it to `clerk:<sub>`.\n\n## Tenant scoping\n`X-Tenant-Id` selects the tenant for a request. Blank = all tenants you belong to. A specific id scopes to it (403 if you're not a member and not an operator).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{clerkJwt}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Global guard: surface gateway/engine auth outcomes clearly.",
          "pm.test('No server error (5xx)', function () {",
          "  pm.expect(pm.response.code, 'status').to.be.below(500);",
          "});",
          "if (pm.response.code === 401) {",
          "  console.log('401 — Clerk token missing/expired. Re-fetch window.Clerk.session.getToken().');",
          "}",
          "if (pm.response.code === 403) {",
          "  console.log('403 — likely NOT onboarded (run Onboard Clerk User) or not a member of X-Tenant-Id.');",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
